{
  "stem": "11882.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We cannot forget Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so they have been really wonderful political figures and have led the nation in a wonderful way.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I want to say, as a person spending much of my time in the last years in Germany, the German people all feel very badly about this.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It only gradually comes upon them in its completeness, you know what I mean?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They begin to realize.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, they pushed it away from them after the war and went to work like mad building up a new country from nothing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And more or less don't bother us-- we're working to rebuild a good Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But now they start writing about it, talking about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the German media work is marvelous that they do.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The research they do into these things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we find out that not only Germany, but many parts of Europe collaborated to some extent-- and not too unwillingly-- with Hitler.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was more convenient.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't protest very much, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I think everyone has to feel a little bit with Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you, in your field now, they're-- they're feeling it so much.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They worry about it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they occupy themselves so much with it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you, in your particular assignment, would probably be interested to know that two men who recently got a prize, a Dr.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Lettel, living near Philadelphia, who has done a lot of helpful work, humane work for Germany after the war, was given an award.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And also a man from Israel-- a very devout Jewish person from Israel, who has done a great deal of research on war crimes and the Holocaust-- were each awarded the so-called Buber-Rosenzweig Prize.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That's for good work on Christian-Jewish understanding of each other.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
